engChrName: November 14th, 11:25AM
engSearchText: November 14th, 11:25AM

engChrName: Whoaaa! Those are big rocks!
engSearchText: Whoaaa! Those are big rocks!
jpnChrName: すっごいねぇ……！
jpnSearchText: すっごいねぇ……！

engChrName: That's called a mountain range. I've seen photos of this one, but it's even more impressive in person.
engSearchText:
That's called a mountain range. I've seen photos of
this one, but it's even more impressive in person.
jpnChrName: 確かに凄いね…… 画像しか見たことなかったけど。
jpnSearchText:
確かに凄いね……
画像しか見たことなかったけど。

engChrName: There are two in this area: the Tianshan Mountains in the north and the Ishgal Mountains in the south.
engSearchText:
There are two in this area: the Tianshan Mountains
in the north and the Ishgal Mountains in the south.
jpnChrName: 大陸中部と東部を隔てる２つの屋根──
jpnSearchText: 大陸中部と東部を隔てる２つの屋根──

engChrName: Both serve as the dividing line between central Zemuria and the East.
engSearchText:
Both serve as the dividing line between central
Zemuria and the East.
jpnChrName: 北の《天山（テンザン）連峰》に、 南の《イシュガル山脈》ですね。
jpnSearchText:
北の《天山（テンザン）連峰》に、
南の《イシュガル山脈》ですね。

engChrName: Aren't they also known as the Solaris Mountains and the Kunlun Mountains?
engSearchText:
Aren't they also known as the Solaris Mountains and
the Kunlun Mountains?
jpnChrName: たしか、それぞれ《ソラリス連峰》に 《崑崙（コンロン）山脈》って別名もあるんですよね？
jpnSearchText:
たしか、それぞれ《ソラリス連峰》に
《崑崙（コンロン）山脈》って別名もあるんですよね？

engChrName: Yes, that's right. People from the East call them Solaris and Kunlun.
engSearchText:
Yes, that's right. People from the East call them
Solaris and Kunlun.
jpnChrName: 西方、東方それぞれの呼び方ですね。
jpnSearchText: 西方、東方それぞれの呼び方ですね。

engChrName: But Tianshan and Ishgal are the officially designated names at the behest of the church.
engSearchText:
But Tianshan and Ishgal are the officially designated
names at the behest of the church.
jpnChrName: どちらも使われていますが、教会主導で 国際的な優先名称が決まったそうです。
jpnSearchText:
どちらも使われていますが、教会主導で
国際的な優先名称が決まったそうです。

engChrName: Ahh. I got'cha. (She probably learned about that in class.)
engSearchText:
Ahh. I got'cha.
(She probably learned about that in class.)
jpnChrName: なるほど…… （なんだかテストに出そうかも。）
jpnSearchText:
なるほど……
（なんだかテストに出そうかも。）

engChrName: It's weird to think that my homeland is just on the other side. It's basically a hop, skip, and a jump away.
engSearchText:
It's weird to think that my homeland is just on the
other side. It's basically a hop, skip, and a jump away.
jpnChrName: ふふ、わたしの故郷はあっちの 向こう側なのでちょっと不思議です。
jpnSearchText:
ふふ、わたしの故郷はあっちの
向こう側なのでちょっと不思議です。

engChrName: You'd have to jump pretty damn high to get over that mountain, though. Your home might as well be in a completely different world.
engSearchText:
You'd have to jump pretty damn high to get over that
mountain, though. Your home might as well be in a
completely different world.
jpnChrName: ま、どっちの山脈も馬鹿デカイから、 反対側はもはや別世界なんだろうが。
jpnSearchText:
ま、どっちの山脈も馬鹿デカイから、
反対側はもはや別世界なんだろうが。

engChrName: Huh?
engSearchText: Huh?
jpnChrName: あん……？
jpnSearchText: あん……？

engChrName: *whistle*!
engSearchText: *whistle*!
jpnChrName: ヒュウ……！
jpnSearchText: ヒュウ……！

engChrName: That bike was super duper cool!
engSearchText: That bike was super duper cool!
jpnChrName: かっくいー！！
jpnSearchText: かっくいー！！

engChrName: Man, I'd kill for a ride like that!
engSearchText: Man, I'd kill for a ride like that!
jpnChrName: いいねェ、イカすバイクじゃねえか！
jpnSearchText: いいねェ、イカすバイクじゃねえか！

engChrName: I thought I saw the ETWS label on it.
engSearchText: I thought I saw the ETWS label on it.
jpnChrName: 車体にＥＴＷＳ（エトワス）って書いてましたね。
jpnSearchText: 車体にＥＴＷＳ（エトワス）って書いてましたね。

engChrName: Good eye. That man was riding one of the high-end models they released in the spring.
engSearchText:
Good eye. That man was riding one of the high-end
models they released in the spring.
jpnChrName: ああ……春に発売された 大型高級導力バイクだったかな？
jpnSearchText:
ああ……春に発売された
大型高級導力バイクだったかな？

engChrName: You have to be quite large to ride one of those, and he was exactly that.
engSearchText:
You have to be quite large to ride one of those, and
he was exactly that.
jpnChrName: なんか凄い体格のヒトが 運転してたみたいだったけど。
jpnSearchText:
なんか凄い体格のヒトが
運転してたみたいだったけど。

engChrName: Indeed. He had an impressive physique for a man of his age.
engSearchText:
Indeed. He had an impressive physique for a man of
his age.
jpnChrName: ええ、それもご高齢の方で いらっしゃったようですね。
jpnSearchText:
ええ、それもご高齢の方で
いらっしゃったようですね。

engChrName: Hmm? Why the long face, Van?
engSearchText: Hmm? Why the long face, Van?
jpnChrName: ？　えっと、ヴァンさん？
jpnSearchText: ？　えっと、ヴァンさん？

engChrName: What's wrong? Are you carsick or something?
engSearchText: What's wrong? Are you carsick or something?
jpnChrName: ヴァン、どしたのー？
jpnSearchText: ヴァン、どしたのー？

engChrName: Nah. Nothin' like that. Just got a bit of trauma with guys who ride around on big bikes.
engSearchText:
Nah. Nothin' like that. Just got a bit of trauma with
guys who ride around on big bikes.
jpnChrName: いや、確かにイカすが 大型バイク乗りにはトラウマがな……
jpnSearchText:
いや、確かにイカすが
大型バイク乗りにはトラウマがな……

engChrName: Oh, and I ain't talkin' about Hermès. She's been a huge help. This issue's exclusive to dudes.
engSearchText:
Oh, and I ain't talkin' about Hermès. She's been a
huge help. This issue's exclusive to dudes.
jpnChrName: エルメスには世話になってるから あくまで野郎限定なんだが……
jpnSearchText:
エルメスには世話になってるから
あくまで野郎限定なんだが……

engChrName: The Direwolf really did a number on your psyche, huh?
engSearchText:
The Direwolf really did a number on your
psyche, huh?
jpnChrName: あはは…… 《痩せ狼》ってヒトですね。
jpnSearchText:
あはは……
《痩せ狼》ってヒトですね。

engChrName: Something about that dude makes me want to deck him in the face. Maybe it's the shades.
engSearchText:
Something about that dude makes me want to deck
him in the face. Maybe it's the shades.
jpnChrName: 黒芒街でツァオと一緒にいた グラサンのヤベぇヤツか。
jpnSearchText:
黒芒街でツァオと一緒にいた
グラサンのヤベぇヤツか。

engChrName: That is inadvisable, Mr. Wei. He has been labeled as an S-class threat by the Marduk Company.
engSearchText:
That is inadvisable, Mr. Wei. He has been labeled as
an S-class threat by the Marduk Company.
jpnChrName: マルドゥック社でも 脅威度評価Ｓランクの人物ですね。
jpnSearchText:
マルドゥック社でも
脅威度評価Ｓランクの人物ですね。

engChrName: Wh-What? You're acquainted with an S-class threat?
engSearchText: Wh-What? You're acquainted with an S-class threat?
jpnChrName: そ、そんなヒトがいるわけ？
jpnSearchText: そ、そんなヒトがいるわけ？

engChrName: Your choice of clientele is...atypical, to say the least.
engSearchText: Your choice of clientele is...atypical, to say the least.
jpnChrName: というかレーサーに女優といい、 この事務所、交友関係怪しすぎない？
jpnSearchText:
というかレーサーに女優といい、
この事務所、交友関係怪しすぎない？

engChrName: (...There's no way it could be him.)
engSearchText: (...There's no way it could be him.)
jpnChrName: （………いや、まさかな。）
jpnSearchText: （………いや、まさかな。）

engChrName: (What a joke. This ain't even my hometown, and yet here I am gettin' all nostalgic over this shit.)
engSearchText:
(What a joke. This ain't even my hometown, and yet
here I am gettin' all nostalgic over this shit.)
jpnChrName: （ったく、故郷ってわけじゃねえのに   ガラにもなく里心がついたか……？）
jpnSearchText:
（ったく、故郷ってわけじゃねえのに
ガラにもなく里心がついたか……？）

engChrName: (Van looks to be lost in thought.)
engSearchText: (Van looks to be lost in thought.)
jpnChrName: （……ヴァンさん、   何かを思い出してるような。）
jpnSearchText:
（……ヴァンさん、
何かを思い出してるような。）

engChrName: (Well, he IS smiling, so maybe I shouldn't worry.)
engSearchText: (Well, he IS smiling, so maybe I shouldn't worry.)
jpnChrName: （それに──ちょっと嬉しそう？）
jpnSearchText: （それに──ちょっと嬉しそう？）

engChrName: Yes, I've left Basel with the documents in hand.
engSearchText: Yes, I've left Basel with the documents in hand.
jpnChrName: ……はい、全て回収を終えて バーゼルを離れました。
jpnSearchText:
……はい、全て回収を終えて
バーゼルを離れました。

engChrName: I also procured the special tools and alloys—even if that WAS outside the scope of the mission...
engSearchText:
I also procured the special tools and alloys—even if
that WAS outside the scope of the mission...
jpnChrName: 特殊な作業工具や合金の調達は 予定にない段取りになりましたけど。
jpnSearchText:
特殊な作業工具や合金の調達は
予定にない段取りになりましたけど。

engChrName: ...but that aside, everything has gone according to plan.
engSearchText:
...but that aside, everything has gone according
to plan.
jpnChrName: ええ、それ以外の事はつつがなく……
jpnSearchText: ええ、それ以外の事はつつがなく……

engChrName: I will have to let you go for a moment. I'll call back shortly.
engSearchText:
I will have to let you go for a moment. I'll call
back shortly.
jpnChrName: ……申し訳ありません、 折り返し連絡します。
jpnSearchText:
……申し訳ありません、
折り返し連絡します。

engChrName: I believe we have found our perpetrator.
engSearchText: I believe we have found our perpetrator.
jpnChrName: 無事に追い付けたようですね。
jpnSearchText: 無事に追い付けたようですね。

engChrName: This is the honeytrap girl? Hmm... Yeah, I'd hit that.
engSearchText: This is the honeytrap girl? Hmm... Yeah, I'd hit that.
jpnChrName: ヒュウ！　ハニートラップを 仕掛けるだけあって上玉じゃねえか。
jpnSearchText:
ヒュウ！　ハニートラップを
仕掛けるだけあって上玉じゃねえか。

engChrName: Oh, dear. I thought my little ruse would have bought me more time.
engSearchText:
Oh, dear. I thought my little ruse would have bought
me more time.
jpnChrName: ……その様子だと、念の為仕掛けておいた “罠”も見透かされてしまったようね。
jpnSearchText:
……その様子だと、念の為仕掛けておいた
“罠”も見透かされてしまったようね。

engChrName: You do not appear to be associated with the police or Marduk.
engSearchText:
You do not appear to be associated with the police
or Marduk.
jpnChrName: 警察でもＭＫの連中でも無さそうだけど、 貴方達は何者なの？
jpnSearchText:
警察でもＭＫの連中でも無さそうだけど、
貴方達は何者なの？

engChrName: Perhaps you might be interested in negotiating? I can offer you a substantial reward if you let me go.
engSearchText:
Perhaps you might be interested in negotiating? I can
offer you a substantial reward if you let me go.
jpnChrName: 場合によっては交渉の余地もあると思うけど。
jpnSearchText: 場合によっては交渉の余地もあると思うけど。

engChrName: Tempting, but nah.
engSearchText: Tempting, but nah.
jpnChrName: 俺達はアンタがトラップにかけた旦那から 依頼を請け負った解決屋だ。
jpnSearchText:
俺達はアンタがトラップにかけた旦那から
依頼を請け負った解決屋だ。

engChrName: Normally I'd be up for a little wheelin' and dealin', but I've got a pair of scrutinizing eyes on me.
engSearchText:
Normally I'd be up for a little wheelin' and dealin',
but I've got a pair of scrutinizing eyes on me.
jpnChrName: 普段なら確かに交渉の余地もあるんだが…… 今日はお目付け役も一緒なんでね。
jpnSearchText:
普段なら確かに交渉の余地もあるんだが……
今日はお目付け役も一緒なんでね。

engChrName: 'Fraid you're just gonna have to hand over the case.
engSearchText: 'Fraid you're just gonna have to hand over the case.
jpnChrName: 大人しくトランクを返してもらう以外の 選択肢は無さそうだ。
jpnSearchText:
大人しくトランクを返してもらう以外の
選択肢は無さそうだ。

engChrName: Just what exactly would you have done had I not tagged along?
engSearchText:
Just what exactly would you have done had I not
tagged along?
jpnChrName: 僕がいなかったら どうするつもりだったんだか……
jpnSearchText:
僕がいなかったら
どうするつもりだったんだか……

engChrName: Oh, my. A researcher from the institute is here, too?
engSearchText: Oh, my. A researcher from the institute is here, too?
jpnChrName: あら、理科大学の研究員まで一緒だったの。
jpnSearchText: あら、理科大学の研究員まで一緒だったの。

engChrName: Well, I'm sorry to disappoint, but the case stays with me. I'll give you two options: go back to Basel empty handed—or return in body bags.
engSearchText:
Well, I'm sorry to disappoint, but the case stays
with me. I'll give you two options: go back to Basel
empty handed—or return in body bags.
jpnChrName: 悪いけど、トランクを返す訳にはいかないわ。 ──交渉決裂って事ね。
jpnSearchText:
悪いけど、トランクを返す訳にはいかないわ。
──交渉決裂って事ね。

engChrName: We will never agree to your terms!
engSearchText: We will never agree to your terms!
jpnChrName: となれば、こちらも実力行使に 出るしかありませんね。
jpnSearchText:
となれば、こちらも実力行使に
出るしかありませんね。

engChrName: I concur. We'll instead opt for the third option: fight!
engSearchText: I concur. We'll instead opt for the third option: fight!
jpnChrName: 僕も援護します──！
jpnSearchText: 僕も援護します──！

engChrName: (That orbal gun design looks eerily familiar. It must be—)
engSearchText:
(That orbal gun design looks eerily familiar. It must
be—)
jpnChrName: （あの特殊な導力銃は確か──）
jpnSearchText: （あの特殊な導力銃は確か──）

engChrName: Well, don't say I didn't warn you.
engSearchText: Well, don't say I didn't warn you.
jpnChrName: ハッ、言っておくけど手を引いた方が身の為よ。
jpnSearchText: ハッ、言っておくけど手を引いた方が身の為よ。

engChrName: What?! She had monsters this whole time?!
engSearchText: What?! She had monsters this whole time?!
jpnChrName: ……！ 魔獣まで用意していたなんて……
jpnSearchText:
……！
魔獣まで用意していたなんて……

engChrName: Someone came prepared.
engSearchText: Someone came prepared.
jpnChrName: 随分と用意周到じゃねえか。
jpnSearchText: 随分と用意周到じゃねえか。

engChrName: Not like it'll make any difference, though. We'll make mincemeat out of 'em in seconds flat.
engSearchText:
Not like it'll make any difference, though. We'll make
mincemeat out of 'em in seconds flat.
jpnChrName: それじゃこっちも行かせてもらうぜ！
jpnSearchText: それじゃこっちも行かせてもらうぜ！

engChrName: No way! How could I possibly have lost?!
engSearchText: No way! How could I possibly have lost?!
jpnChrName: そんな……！ あの戦力で押し負けるだなんて……！
jpnSearchText:
そんな……！
あの戦力で押し負けるだなんて……！

engChrName: Checkmate. Now give up the goods.
engSearchText: Checkmate. Now give up the goods.
jpnChrName: これで“詰み”だな。 コイツは返してもらうぜ。
jpnSearchText:
これで“詰み”だな。
コイツは返してもらうぜ。

engChrName: And while you're at it, answer me this: what organization do you belong to? Who hired you?
engSearchText:
And while you're at it, answer me this: what
organization do you belong to? Who hired you?
jpnChrName: 貴方はどこの組織の人間なんですか？ もしくは、誰に雇われたのか答えて下さい。
jpnSearchText:
貴方はどこの組織の人間なんですか？
もしくは、誰に雇われたのか答えて下さい。

engChrName: I can answer that in her stead. I recognize that particular gun model.
engSearchText:
I can answer that in her stead. I recognize that
particular gun model.
jpnChrName: 彼女が使用していた銃には見覚えがあります──
jpnSearchText: 彼女が使用していた銃には見覚えがあります──

engChrName: She's likely associated with Zecht Arms.
engSearchText: She's likely associated with Zecht Arms.
jpnChrName: 恐らくこの方は《ゼクトアームズ》でしょう。
jpnSearchText: 恐らくこの方は《ゼクトアームズ》でしょう。

engChrName: You mean that new weapons manufacturer?
engSearchText: You mean that new weapons manufacturer?
jpnChrName: 《ゼクトアームズ》って…… 新興武器メーカーの、あの？
jpnSearchText:
《ゼクトアームズ》って……
新興武器メーカーの、あの？

engChrName: If I'm remembering things right, their name started makin' the rounds during the war with the Empire.
engSearchText:
If I'm remembering things right, their name started
makin' the rounds during the war with the Empire.
jpnChrName: 確か、帝国との大戦あたりから 名前を聞くようになった会社だよな。
jpnSearchText:
確か、帝国との大戦あたりから
名前を聞くようになった会社だよな。

engChrName: Correct. They are similar to Marduk in some respects. Although, they are not nearly as large an enterprise.
engSearchText:
Correct. They are similar to Marduk in
some respects. Although, they are not nearly as large
an enterprise.
jpnChrName: ええ、遠く及ばないながらも ＭＫ社と似た側面も持ち合わせているようですね。
jpnSearchText:
ええ、遠く及ばないながらも
ＭＫ社と似た側面も持ち合わせているようですね。

engChrName: Their ambitions for weapons development, however, are quite ferocious. They've been aggressive with expanding their market share of late.
engSearchText:
Their ambitions for weapons development, however,
are quite ferocious. They've been aggressive with
expanding their market share of late.
jpnChrName: 特に武器開発に野心的で、 それなりにシェアを拡大しているそうです。
jpnSearchText:
特に武器開発に野心的で、
それなりにシェアを拡大しているそうです。

engChrName: And now they're sendin' out spies to do their dirty work? Damn. That's low.
engSearchText:
And now they're sendin' out spies to do their
dirty work? Damn. That's low.
jpnChrName: で、そんな武器メーカー様が 産業スパイをしに来たっていう訳か。
jpnSearchText:
で、そんな武器メーカー様が
産業スパイをしに来たっていう訳か。

engChrName: I can't say I disagree. Stealing technology from competitors is hardly an ethical business practice.
engSearchText:
I can't say I disagree. Stealing technology from
competitors is hardly an ethical business practice.
jpnChrName: 他メーカーから技術を盗もうなんて 随分と立派な経営方針ですね。
jpnSearchText:
他メーカーから技術を盗もうなんて
随分と立派な経営方針ですね。

engChrName: Tch...
engSearchText: Tch...
engHtmlText: ゼクトアームズのスパイ

engChrName: Now, then. I suppose we'd better get this stuff back to our client.
engSearchText:
Now, then. I suppose we'd better get this stuff back to
our client.
jpnChrName: さて……荷物の確認やら何やら、 依頼主にやってもらう必要があるだろう。
jpnSearchText:
さて……荷物の確認やら何やら、
依頼主にやってもらう必要があるだろう。

engChrName: We should also take her back with us. Could you restrain her for me, Ferida?
engSearchText:
We should also take her back with us. Could you
restrain her for me, Ferida?
jpnChrName: とりあえずコイツを連れて街に戻るぞ。 拘束の方は頼んだぜ。
jpnSearchText:
とりあえずコイツを連れて街に戻るぞ。
拘束の方は頼んだぜ。

engChrName: On it!
engSearchText: On it!
jpnChrName: 任せて下さい！
jpnSearchText: 任せて下さい！
